com.microsoft.azure.iothub.transport.amqps

Class AmqpsSenderHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.qpid.proton.engine.BaseHandler
      • com.microsoft.azure.iothub.transport.amqps.AmqpsSenderHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.qpid.proton.engine.Handler

    public class AmqpsSenderHandler
extends org.apache.qpid.proton.engine.BaseHandler
    Instance of the QPID-Proton-J BaseHandler class overriding the events needed to handle sending operations. Contains and sets connection parameters, maintains the layers of the AMQP protocol and creates and sets SASL authentication for the transport.

      • AmqpsSenderHandler

        public AmqpsSenderHandler(String hostName,
                          String userName,
                          String deviceID,
                          String sasToken)
        Constructor to set up connection parameters and initialize handshaker for the transport.
        Parameters:
        hostName - address string of the IoT Hub (example: AAA.BBB.CCC)
        userName - username string to use SASL authentication (example: user@sas.[hostName])
        deviceID - ID from which this senderHandler communicates
        sasToken - SAS token string
